snippet.title: How to Kickstart Your Software Engineering Career
snippet.description:
Designed to help new folks coming into the tech industry for their first full time role (or as an intern!), we'll talk about how to step into your job confidently through a variety of topics! We talk about the non-technical, more human, nuanced aspects of kickstarting your Software Engineering career, by discussing:
- How to start your first day on the right foot
- Learning important communication skills, like public speaking listening, and empathy
- Understand how to navigate relationship between yourself, your manager, and teammates thoughtfully
- Begin to identify and work towards achieving your career goals
- Learn how to network at meetups, conferences, and in the online community
- Create a healthy relationship with your work
- Start to monitor your mental and emotional health while working as a Software Engineer
